oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Thurman Banks
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Mrs. Thurman Banks, her daughter Nell Ruth Banks, and a visiting girl, Pauline Lowe, are proudly looking at the 200 baby chicks just acquired for their second brood this year. These chickens were part of the Home Food Supply Program.
The Home Food Supply Program was a war-relief program instituted by the administration of Gov. Prentice Cooper.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
